  comm:now this suta is 1 of those sutas if you think carefully about it now he has very far implications here the buddha is saying that there are 5 types of aryans who attain ibana in the human existence there are 3 types of sotapanna described here the first type is 1 who has 7 more rebirths at the most then the second type is 1 who is reborn among noble families 2 or 3 times and the third type of sotapanna is 1 who just takes 1 rebirth as a man and then makes an end of dukkhala uh so there are 3 types of sota panna and then the saka the garmin is the ones returner and that is the second fruit are then the last 1 is arahan these are those who attain ibana in the human existence now this utah firstly yeah the first implication is that all aryans have right view this is confirmed in others with tesla but how does 1 attain right view in the majima nikaya sutra 43 it is said that right view is attained by listening to the dhamma and then having yoni so mana sikhara is the other condition yoni means the ability to have terror consideration or thorough contemplation that means a person's mind is fairly clear so that he can consider tara lila and so you can see here all the buddha's disciples who are aryans they listen to the dhamma first to get right viewed that's why the buddha's disciples are called savakas meaning hearers or listeners now so this 5 types of aryans attain nibana in this life the other 5 type of aryans who attain ibana after leaving here there are 5 types described here all of them are anagaminza are generally reborn in the sudavasa abode the fourth jhana heavens and from there they enter nibana so if they enter nibana from there that means they don't become arahants you know they don't become arahants they just enter nibana upon passing away because it is said here that all arahansa enter nibana as a human being now this this uh contradicts the abi dharmala because in the abhidharma it is stated that when the buddha taught the abhidharma millions of devas attain arahant now if they attain arhan hood as devas that means they will enter they will enter nibana as an arahant deva but the buddha says here that all arahants are humans that is why you notice that all buddhas come to the human plane to teach the dhamma buddhas are never reborn in heaven to teach the devas always come to the human plane now this implication of sotapanna and attaining nibana this has never been well explained in buddhist texts and here we see that there are some who have 7 more rebirths after 7 more rebirths and they when they pass away and they anthony barna and there are some who come back to the human plane and reborn as a noble in the noble family 2 or 3 times and then they enter nibana then the last type is 1 who is who takes 1 more birth as a human being and then enters nirvana now this last 1 is quite interesting because he has only 1 human birth as a human being and we know from other sutas for example angutta nikaya 3.85 that the sota panna the first fruit arya and the sakadagamin the second fruit area they only have perfect moral conduct they only have perfect sila they don't have samadhi and paneer whereas the anagamin the third fruit arya has perfect sila and perfect samadhi against jhana and the arahan has perfect sila samadhi and panya so sothapana having only sila how does he enter nirvana we see from the buddha's own experience in the gatikara suta majimanikaya that the buddha in a previous life was born as a brahmin jyotipala and there he met the buddha kasapa and then when the buddha kasapa taught him the dhamma he changed completely from having no respect for the buddha he became a disciple of the buddha and renounce and became a monk so from there we can see a very probably the buddha in that lifetime as jyoti palla had attained sothapana and then after that he followed the buddha as a monk and he attained jana why we say he attained jana because when he was reborn in his last life as a human being he said that when he was very young he attained the first jana under the jambu tree so for him so young not to attain jana that means previous life he had already attained jana that means very probably under buddha kasapa he attained jana so if he had attained janna very probably also he became a saka dagamin and after becoming a saka dagamin he went to the tusita heaven and after the tusita heaven he came down to the human existence for the very last time so we can see here from here of the buddha's example that probably yeah all arahants sorry all buddhas because buddhas are self enlightened beings you know destroy very hard like our buddha and they became enlightened and there is something in them from the previous life and that makes them strive very hard which is then that something must be that they have already become arya in the previous life so from this utah we find that sutapanaza since they they attain ibana in this lifetime that means some of them are at least would attain especially for example the the last type of the 1 who comes back 1 sunni as a human being probably yeah he strives and then attains arahan hood or buddha and then enters nibanala so the same with sakura the garmin sucker the garmin also because they come back only once as a human being very probably that last time they strive and then they attain all buddha and then anthony barna and then the other 5 who attain uh nibana in in the heavens this these the 5 types of anagamin there is a simile given in some other suta on the uh anagamin it is stated now is like a piece of heated metal you know which a blacksmith is hitting a blacksmith is he hitting a red hot piece of metal and then a chip of iron flies over and this chip of iron flies off to the ground and then it cools down and that is a simile for an anagaming that means an anagamin he goes to the sudabasa abode and cools down there and enters nibana so there are some undergarments who when they go to the sudabasa abodes uh the fourth jana heavens they s